  "prompt": "Which is the best website for booking cheap air tickets?",
  "response": "Finding the best website for booking cheap air tickets can vary depending on your location, the airline preference, and the type of trip you're planning. However, here are some popular options that are frequently recommended:\n\n1. **Skyscanner**: Known for its user-friendly interface and comprehensive search options, Skyscanner allows you to compare prices across various airlines and booking sites.\n\n2. **Google Flights**: Google Flights offers a powerful search tool and flexible date options. It also provides price tracking and insights to help you find the best deals.\n\n3. **Kayak**: Kayak aggregates prices from hundreds of travel sites and offers tools like fare alerts and price forecasts to help you book at the right time.\n\n4. **Momondo**: Momondo is praised for its extensive search capabilities and transparent comparison of flight fares from numerous airlines and travel agencies.\n\n5. **Expedia**: Expedia not only offers flights but also package deals that include hotels and car rentals, often at discounted rates.\n\n6. **CheapOair**: As the name suggests, CheapOair focuses on finding budget-friendly tickets and offers deals and discounts that can be beneficial for travelers trying to save money.\n\n7. **Hopper**: Hopper analyzes billions of flight prices daily and uses historical data to predict future deals, allowing you to book at the optimal time.\n\n8. **Priceline**: Priceline offers unique features like \"Name Your Own Price,\" though such features are less common now than they used to be. Still, it remains competitive for finding cheap flights.\n\nRemember to check multiple sites and use tools like fare alerts, flexible date searches, and price predictors to get the best deal.",
